WEBVTT

00:07.310 --> 00:10.206
[chill music]

00:10.275 --> 00:17.310
♪ ♪

00:17.379 --> 00:20.172
- And who was Rosa's brother
named after?

00:20.241 --> 00:23.482
- Her Uncle Arturo.
- Big mistake.

00:23.551 --> 00:25.758
[both laugh]

00:27.862 --> 00:29.620
- Where did the two
of you first meet?

00:29.689 --> 00:31.965
- I've never actually
met Arturo.

00:32.034 --> 00:33.689
He lives in Oaxaca.

00:33.758 --> 00:35.034
- Oh, he meant us, honey.

00:35.103 --> 00:36.413
- Oh, sorry.

00:36.482 --> 00:38.275
Fort Sam Houston,
AI Training.

00:38.344 --> 00:40.103
They put us in the line
together, the first thing.

00:40.172 --> 00:42.137
- Thank God he didn't fall
for one of the guys

00:42.206 --> 00:43.827
on the line instead of me.

00:43.896 --> 00:45.103
[both laugh]

00:45.172 --> 00:46.758
- All right.

00:46.827 --> 00:49.310
We, uh, we planned
to get married stateside,

00:49.379 --> 00:51.413
but obviously her MAVNI
status being revoked

00:51.482 --> 00:54.724
moved those plans, so we got
married in-country instead.

00:54.793 --> 00:59.620
And after dodging bullets
and saving lives,

00:59.689 --> 01:01.034
here we are.

01:01.103 --> 01:02.689
- Here we are.

01:02.758 --> 01:05.482
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

01:08.344 --> 01:11.482
- Knock off the bullshit.

01:11.551 --> 01:13.620
- Excuse us?

01:16.689 --> 01:22.344
- Just have one final question
for the both of you.

01:24.827 --> 01:26.586
- What's that, sir?

01:26.655 --> 01:29.137
- Tell me how you really feel
about each other.

01:32.241 --> 01:35.379
- Perhaps we're laying it on
a bit thick, sweetie.

01:35.448 --> 01:37.344
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:37.413 --> 01:39.241
- Sorry, you know,
it's just this--

01:39.310 --> 01:40.793
it's pretty nerve-wracking

01:40.862 --> 01:42.620
and I just assumed that
you wanted to hear

01:42.689 --> 01:44.620
all the good stuff, so...
- Yeah.

01:44.689 --> 01:47.448
- Look, the truth is that we
love each other very much.

01:48.758 --> 01:51.172
But being married
is fucking hard.

01:51.241 --> 01:52.827
- Hardest thing
we've ever done.

01:52.896 --> 01:54.310
- And we spent
so much time together.

01:54.379 --> 01:57.344
- We started to drive
each other crazy.

01:57.413 --> 02:00.310
- I think this is going
to take a real effort.

02:00.379 --> 02:02.448
- But we're gonna make it.

02:06.103 --> 02:08.620
- And if you're married, sir,
and you have any marriage hacks

02:08.689 --> 02:10.896
to send our way,
we'd really appreciate it.

02:10.965 --> 02:15.103
- You know, to keep us
from killing each other.

02:15.172 --> 02:17.241
- No more questions.

02:24.724 --> 02:28.103
So...

02:28.172 --> 02:30.172
It is my pleasure
as an emissary

02:30.241 --> 02:31.724
of the U.S. State
Department

02:31.793 --> 02:33.724
to welcome you as a legal
permanent resident

02:33.793 --> 02:36.068
of the United States
of America, Mrs. Roback.

02:36.137 --> 02:37.827
- Oh, it's Alvarez.
I'm keeping my name.

02:37.896 --> 02:39.655
- Yeah, I'm not thrilled
but, you know,

02:39.724 --> 02:42.310
she says Rosa Roback
sounds like a skin disease.

02:42.379 --> 02:44.655
- Yeah.
- It does.

02:44.724 --> 02:46.793
- [sighs]

02:46.862 --> 02:48.896
- Congratulations.
- Thank you so much, sir.

02:48.965 --> 02:51.689
- Thank you.
- Have a beautiful day.

02:51.758 --> 02:55.000
It worked!
You're amazing

02:55.068 --> 02:56.310
Oh, God!
- Of course it worked.

02:56.379 --> 02:58.068
It was too fucking insane
not to work.

02:58.137 --> 03:01.448
- You're the best!
- [chuckles]

03:01.517 --> 03:03.724
- It's still gonna take three
to six months

03:03.793 --> 03:05.724
for my Green Card
to get processed.

03:05.793 --> 03:08.758
What do we do until then?
- We act like husband and wife.

03:08.827 --> 03:10.862
- And after I get it?
- Not sure.

03:10.931 --> 03:12.551
We might have to keep it up
for a little while.

03:12.620 --> 03:14.241
I hear they check on you once
every so often.

03:14.310 --> 03:17.517
- Yeah, every few years.
- Yeah.

03:17.586 --> 03:21.724
- That's a long time.
- Yeah, it is.

03:21.793 --> 03:24.241
Now that you say it.

03:24.310 --> 03:26.620
- We really
are fucking married.

03:26.689 --> 03:29.793
- Yeah.

03:29.862 --> 03:32.034
Guess it wasn't an act.

03:32.103 --> 03:34.655
- No.
[chuckles]

03:34.724 --> 03:36.448
- I'm gonna make you
a great husband.

03:36.517 --> 03:38.965
- And I'm gonna make you
a great wife.

03:39.724 --> 03:42.689
- Yo!
New recruit in the house.

03:44.448 --> 03:47.137
- I'm gonna have to rescind
my application

03:47.206 --> 03:49.620
with your organization.

03:49.689 --> 03:51.413
- Why?

03:51.482 --> 03:54.103
- Recent events
have forced me to reconsider.

03:54.172 --> 03:55.896
- Recent events?

03:55.965 --> 03:57.551
- Turns out I'm not cut out

03:57.620 --> 03:59.103
for threatening people
with violence

03:59.172 --> 04:01.655
if they don't leave
their home.

04:01.724 --> 04:03.241
- It's not that simple.

04:03.310 --> 04:06.206
- Afraid it is to me.

04:06.275 --> 04:09.241
- We do important work
that I can't fully explain

04:09.310 --> 04:10.931
until you're on the inside.

04:11.000 --> 04:12.689
But once you are,

04:12.758 --> 04:14.724
you'll see that there's
a purpose behind all of it.

04:14.793 --> 04:17.206
- That may be true,
but I'm still gonna have

04:17.275 --> 04:18.965
to choose to stay
on the outside.

04:19.034 --> 04:22.241
- You realize you can't
keep the sign-up bonus, right?

04:22.310 --> 04:24.862
- All to keenly aware of that.

04:24.931 --> 04:26.827
- Is your family?

04:26.896 --> 04:29.689
I assume they still
need the cash

04:29.758 --> 04:32.482
- That they do.

04:32.551 --> 04:34.965
- Everyone out.

04:39.586 --> 04:43.931
[indistinct chattering]

04:45.896 --> 04:47.551
- Catch.

04:50.448 --> 04:52.103
- What's this?

04:52.172 --> 04:53.655
- The future.

04:53.724 --> 04:57.275
[suspenseful music]

04:57.344 --> 05:00.793
♪ ♪

05:00.862 --> 05:03.724
- What if you end up
hating me?

05:05.448 --> 05:07.620
- What if you end up
hating me?

05:07.689 --> 05:09.758
- We'll just have to work
super hard

05:09.827 --> 05:11.827
to make sure
that doesn't happen.

05:11.896 --> 05:13.689
- Okay.

05:13.758 --> 05:16.034
- Okay.

05:16.103 --> 05:18.793
- We should be fine
as long as you keep

05:18.862 --> 05:21.448
your expectations of me
pretty low.

05:21.517 --> 05:23.034
- Then this marriage
will thrive.

05:23.103 --> 05:24.586
- [chuckles]

05:24.655 --> 05:28.758
- Hey.
How'd it go?

05:28.827 --> 05:30.827
- I'm a permanent legal
resident

05:30.896 --> 05:32.551
of the United States
of America!

05:32.620 --> 05:34.586
- Fuck yeah!
Nice!

05:34.655 --> 05:36.241
- How'd it go with you?

05:36.310 --> 05:37.551
- I hate dealing with OSI.

05:37.620 --> 05:39.344
You know, they always
look at you suspiciously

05:39.413 --> 05:40.931
like it's you who just
committed the crime.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.482
- Bus is loading.

05:43.551 --> 05:44.620
- Austin's getting ready
to make his move

05:44.689 --> 05:46.000
against SecCorp, huh?

05:46.068 --> 05:49.655
- Yeah, just filed the
preliminary documents for him.

05:49.724 --> 05:52.965
- What a great fucking day.

05:54.517 --> 05:56.379
- This really that valuable?

05:56.448 --> 05:58.379
- Depends.
- On what?

05:58.448 --> 06:01.172
- On if you wanna use
a cell phone,

06:01.241 --> 06:03.931
power up a computer,
drive a car.

06:04.000 --> 06:05.379
- And it's all just sitting
right there

06:05.448 --> 06:07.137
underneath the village?

06:07.206 --> 06:09.413
- Geologists think it might be
the largest deposit of Lithium

06:09.482 --> 06:10.689
found on this planet.

06:10.758 --> 06:12.655
- Why are you telling me
all this?

06:12.724 --> 06:14.517
- Because I'm tasked with
putting the team together

06:14.586 --> 06:16.482
to get this job done.

06:16.551 --> 06:19.413
All those other lug heads
are just muscle.

06:19.482 --> 06:20.965
I need brains,

06:21.034 --> 06:22.931
and as hard as it is
for me to admit,

06:23.000 --> 06:24.965
guys like you and Roback
are not dumb.

06:25.034 --> 06:26.551
- Roback?

06:26.620 --> 06:28.137
You know he's not getting
on board.

06:28.206 --> 06:30.655
- After he sees how good
SecCorp is for you,

06:30.724 --> 06:33.000
he might change
his opinion on us.

06:33.068 --> 06:34.344
- But you hate him.

06:34.413 --> 06:36.551
- That I do,

06:36.620 --> 06:41.000
but the man I work
for has his reasons.

06:41.068 --> 06:42.724
- Never gonna happen.

06:42.793 --> 06:44.448
Whatever's
underneath that village

06:44.517 --> 06:47.241
belongs to the people
of the village.

06:47.310 --> 06:49.655
- You don't think that
the Russians or the Chinese

06:49.724 --> 06:51.862
would do the exact same thing
we're doing?

06:51.931 --> 06:54.379
All the company that hired us
wants us to do

06:54.448 --> 06:55.965
is clear out that village
so they can start

06:56.034 --> 06:57.965
mining this stuff
as quickly as possible.

07:00.793 --> 07:02.931
- Sorry, but I can't do
to the people of that village

07:03.000 --> 07:04.620
what the bank is doing
to my family.

07:04.689 --> 07:07.551
- Everyone on my team
has been guaranteed a share.

07:07.620 --> 07:09.344
Should be enough money
to really help out

07:09.413 --> 07:11.137
you and your family.

07:11.206 --> 07:13.206
♪ ♪

07:13.275 --> 07:14.655
- I'll get back to you.

07:14.724 --> 07:17.068
♪ ♪

07:17.137 --> 07:20.241
[jet engine revs]

07:20.310 --> 07:23.793
- I can't believe this marriage
idea of yours actually worked.

07:23.862 --> 07:26.827
- None of you believed in me.
Shame on you all.

07:26.896 --> 07:28.896
- Now all we have to do
is find a ton of people

07:28.965 --> 07:30.689
to marry the rest
of my family.

07:30.758 --> 07:32.620
- Yeah, how is that going?

07:32.689 --> 07:34.689
- The only shot I have
at helping my family

07:34.758 --> 07:36.655
is to hire
an immigration lawyer,

07:36.724 --> 07:39.241
and they're crazy expensive.

07:39.310 --> 07:41.655
- We could use some of those
reconstruction funds

07:41.724 --> 07:43.413
you guys keep in that safe.

07:43.482 --> 07:46.758
- That is a terrible idea.
- Yeah, you're right.

07:46.827 --> 07:50.379
Not gonna ask you to spend the
rest of your life in prison.

07:50.448 --> 07:51.827
- Appreciate it.

07:51.896 --> 07:53.862
Besides, there are trackers
on those bills.

07:53.931 --> 07:55.206
- Trackers?

07:55.275 --> 07:57.241
- Yeah, when they fall
into enemy hands.

07:57.310 --> 07:59.379
- You know, sometimes
they distribute it

07:59.448 --> 08:01.172
to the Taliban on purpose

08:01.241 --> 08:03.827
just so they can track down
their locations.

08:05.413 --> 08:06.862
- Who does the tracking?

08:06.931 --> 08:08.586
- Special Investigations here
at Bagram.

08:08.655 --> 08:11.137
I just dealt with them this
morning for Colonel Austin.

08:11.206 --> 08:13.379
[soft rock music]

08:13.448 --> 08:15.724
- Yeah, we--we have to go.

08:17.793 --> 08:19.379
Come on.
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

08:19.448 --> 08:20.724
- Let's go.
We gotta go.

08:20.793 --> 08:22.413
- We're gonna miss our Chalk!

08:22.482 --> 08:23.586
- Yeah, we're gonna miss
our Chalk.

08:23.655 --> 08:24.724
- Where are you going?

08:24.793 --> 08:25.862
- We're gonna reunite us with

08:25.931 --> 08:26.965
a quarter of a million dollars.

08:27.034 --> 08:28.931
Come on!
- Oh, my God.

08:29.000 --> 08:30.517
So all the money
just fell out of the bird?

08:30.586 --> 08:31.862
- Look, it was a little bit

08:31.931 --> 08:33.689
more complicated than that,
but yeah.

08:33.758 --> 08:35.310
- I cannot believe you didn't
tell me any of this.

08:35.379 --> 08:37.379
- I didn't wanna relive it.
- I can see why.

08:37.448 --> 08:39.103
- And no one wants it back?
- As far as they were concerned

08:39.172 --> 08:40.448
we used it to secure
the morphine.

08:40.517 --> 08:42.103
Nobody asked any questions.

08:42.172 --> 08:44.793
- That is the last time
I give you $250,000 in cash.

08:44.862 --> 08:47.241
- It wasn't a good day.

08:47.310 --> 08:48.724
- Hey, wait here.

08:48.793 --> 08:50.655
They'll be more receptive
if it's just me.

08:50.724 --> 08:51.965
- What are you gonna tell 'em?

08:52.034 --> 08:53.896
- Hmm, that we're trying
to track down

08:53.965 --> 08:55.655
a quarter million dollars
of government money

08:55.724 --> 08:57.103
so we can keep it all
to ourselves.

08:57.172 --> 08:58.482
Don't worry what
I'm gonna tell 'em.

08:58.551 --> 09:00.034
Sit.

09:00.103 --> 09:01.965
Hi.

09:02.034 --> 09:04.275
[suspenseful music]

09:04.344 --> 09:08.172
♪ ♪

09:08.241 --> 09:10.172
- We've been waiting for you
to wake up.

09:10.241 --> 09:12.586
- Please get me out
of this bed.

09:12.655 --> 09:14.206
- Your scans say no fractures,

09:14.275 --> 09:15.827
but we're doing
a concussion protocol.

09:15.896 --> 09:17.344
We'll keep an eye on you

09:17.413 --> 09:19.172
so we can rule out
a subdural hemorrhage.

09:19.241 --> 09:20.724
- It's just a hematoma.

09:20.793 --> 09:23.413
- Hmm, that's not what
your doctor says.

09:23.482 --> 09:25.344
- My doctor?

09:25.413 --> 09:27.068
[door opens]

09:27.137 --> 09:29.206
- Colonel Austin asked
for a second opinion

09:29.275 --> 09:31.689
from a doctor with more
combat experience.

09:31.758 --> 09:33.206
- When I heard you
were chasing Purple Hearts,

09:33.275 --> 09:35.172
I commandeered
the first bird I could.

09:35.241 --> 09:37.655
I wanted to see for myself
that you're still in one piece.

09:37.724 --> 09:40.620
- I'm fine, Dad.

09:41.931 --> 09:44.206
Tell him I'm fine.

09:45.068 --> 09:46.862
- The man has been performing
combat surgeries

09:46.931 --> 09:48.275
since I was in my nappies.

09:48.344 --> 09:50.827
He'll decide
if you're fine or not.

09:50.896 --> 09:52.413
If you need me, sir,

09:52.482 --> 09:54.206
I will be off pretending
to be doing something

09:54.275 --> 09:55.896
more important.

09:56.965 --> 09:58.620
- Heard you extended
your deployment.

09:58.689 --> 10:00.310
- From who?

10:00.379 --> 10:02.448
- Will.
- Who?

10:02.517 --> 10:04.896
- Your husband.

10:04.965 --> 10:07.000
- General Holloway, sir.

10:07.068 --> 10:09.827
- Colonel, thanks for getting
word to me so quickly.

10:09.896 --> 10:11.724
- What's the prognosis?

10:11.793 --> 10:13.241
- She should be up and about

10:13.310 --> 10:15.344
and arguing with her father
again in no time.

10:15.413 --> 10:17.379
- Glad to hear it.

10:17.448 --> 10:19.344
Later you and I need
to download what happened

10:19.413 --> 10:21.103
in that village last night.

10:21.172 --> 10:23.206
- Yes, sir.

10:23.275 --> 10:25.000
- Sir?

10:26.793 --> 10:29.586
- Afraid you're gonna need
to download with me too, Sonia.

10:29.655 --> 10:31.689
[soft rock music]

10:31.758 --> 10:33.793
[sighs]

10:33.862 --> 10:37.517
♪ ♪

10:37.586 --> 10:38.896
- [sighs]

10:38.965 --> 10:41.172
She's been up there
a long time.

10:44.344 --> 10:47.379
- Yeah.

10:47.448 --> 10:50.931
We should probably talk about
Durkin tonight.

10:51.551 --> 10:53.137
- No.

10:53.206 --> 10:55.827
No, that's between you and her.

10:55.896 --> 10:58.758
- That's the thing,
it's kinda not.

10:58.827 --> 11:01.068
You know, it's kinda between
all of us now.

11:03.827 --> 11:06.931
- Yeah.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.724
- Hopefully it'll all work
itself eventually, right?

11:09.793 --> 11:12.172
- Yeah, sure.

11:12.241 --> 11:13.862
Hey.
- Hey, how'd it go?

11:13.931 --> 11:15.620
- Good.
We need to get back to base.

11:15.689 --> 11:18.000
I gotta look up the serial
numbers of the bills I gave you

11:18.068 --> 11:20.068
then I send those to my friend,
she looks up the coordinates,

11:20.137 --> 11:21.793
and she tries to locate them.

11:21.862 --> 11:24.000
If they're out there,
it'll send off the signal.

11:24.068 --> 11:25.689
- Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

11:25.758 --> 11:28.862
- Can we trust this person?

11:28.931 --> 11:30.551
- I told her the money
was given

11:30.620 --> 11:31.862
to some Afghan Nationals

11:31.931 --> 11:34.517
suspected of colluding
with ISIS, so...

11:34.586 --> 11:35.931
- That's a really good story.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.482
- The truth is
she doesn't give a shit.

11:37.551 --> 11:39.448
It's not her money
and they don't get paid dick.

11:39.517 --> 11:41.413
Let's go.

11:41.482 --> 11:43.275
♪ ♪

11:43.344 --> 11:44.965
- Guess I shouldn't
be surprised.

11:45.034 --> 11:46.413
You've always been one
to sacrifice

11:46.482 --> 11:47.931
for what you believed in.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.137
- You have nobody to blame
but yourself for that.

11:51.206 --> 11:54.965
- Oh yeah,
throw it on the old man.

11:55.034 --> 11:57.896
At least I was around long
enough to teach you that.

11:57.965 --> 12:00.103
- Yeah, we all used to joke
that we were raised by

12:00.172 --> 12:02.551
a telephone pretending
to be our father.

12:02.620 --> 12:05.862
- Yeah, I should've been
home more.

12:05.931 --> 12:09.103
- Obviously, I had nothing but
pride for what you were doing.

12:09.172 --> 12:11.275
I followed in your footsteps.

12:11.344 --> 12:14.448
- More than we can say
for your brothers.

12:14.517 --> 12:17.137
- It was easier being
your daughter.

12:18.172 --> 12:19.931
This isn't gonna happen again.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.896
- What if it does?

12:21.965 --> 12:24.103
What about your family?

12:24.172 --> 12:27.275
I don't want you to make
the same mistake I did.

12:27.344 --> 12:29.344
I can make calls.

12:29.413 --> 12:31.689
I can have you relocated
somewhere safer.

12:31.758 --> 12:34.758
A VA hospital close to home

12:34.827 --> 12:36.827
where you can be
with your family.

12:40.068 --> 12:43.103
- I do miss my boys.

12:43.172 --> 12:45.310
- Say the word and I'll do it.

12:45.379 --> 12:47.482
[somber music]

12:47.551 --> 12:50.793
- [sighs]

12:50.862 --> 12:56.172
♪ ♪

13:03.965 --> 13:06.689
- Hey.

13:06.758 --> 13:09.965
- [sighs]
How'd it go with Alvarez?

13:11.310 --> 13:13.275
- She's getting her Green Card.

13:13.344 --> 13:16.068
- Finally,
some good news today.

13:17.655 --> 13:19.586
- Why are you sitting here
all alone in the dark?

13:21.137 --> 13:24.034
- Hiding for my life.

13:25.965 --> 13:28.172
- Does not sound like fun.

13:28.241 --> 13:29.896
- Please turn
the light back off

13:29.965 --> 13:32.620
and exit the way
you came in.

13:32.689 --> 13:34.310
- Not gonna do that.

13:36.275 --> 13:39.137
- You know what this whole
SecCorp thing is about?

13:40.517 --> 13:42.827
- No.

13:42.896 --> 13:46.724
- Fucking rare earth metals.

13:46.793 --> 13:48.793
Gonna be worth more than oil,

13:48.862 --> 13:52.413
and apparently the ground
is lousy with it out here.

13:54.241 --> 13:56.413
- Jesus.

13:56.482 --> 13:58.517
I knew there was a reason
we were fighting this war.

13:58.586 --> 14:02.655
- A lot of money at stake
for just about everybody.

14:02.724 --> 14:05.827
- Yeah, there usually is
when SecCorp's involved.

14:05.896 --> 14:08.034
- I got no other choice

14:08.103 --> 14:11.551
but to go through
with this SecCorp deal.

14:11.620 --> 14:16.551
I'm just working up the stomach
to tell Sasquatch I'm in.

14:16.620 --> 14:20.965
♪ ♪

14:21.034 --> 14:22.655
Go ahead.
Go ahead.

14:22.724 --> 14:25.827
Rip into me.
Let me have it.

14:25.896 --> 14:28.241
♪ ♪

14:28.310 --> 14:32.241
- [sighs]
I totally understand.

14:32.310 --> 14:34.896
- You do?

14:34.965 --> 14:36.482
- Family is more important.

14:36.551 --> 14:39.241
- [sighs]
It is.

14:39.310 --> 14:41.862
- I know.
[chuckles]

14:41.931 --> 14:47.896
♪ ♪

14:47.965 --> 14:50.413
- [sighs]

14:50.482 --> 14:52.275
♪ ♪

14:52.344 --> 14:54.275
- Just do me one last favor

14:54.344 --> 14:56.517
before you put
the black vest on, okay?

14:56.586 --> 14:58.344
- What's that?

14:58.413 --> 15:01.310
- Stop playing with your balls
and come with me.

15:02.827 --> 15:05.758
[suspenseful music]

15:05.827 --> 15:08.551
♪ ♪

15:08.620 --> 15:10.448
Come on.

15:10.517 --> 15:17.000
♪ ♪

15:19.862 --> 15:21.482
What's happening?

15:21.551 --> 15:23.482
- I'm waiting on a response
from a person at OSI.

15:23.551 --> 15:25.172
- What do they use?

15:25.241 --> 15:27.275
Some kind of encrypted fibers
on the bills or something?

15:27.344 --> 15:29.103
- Nah, it's just the bands
that wrap the stacks,

15:29.172 --> 15:31.344
but once those are off,
the money's gone.

15:31.413 --> 15:33.586
- What are we waiting for now?

15:33.655 --> 15:35.413
- We're just waiting.

15:35.482 --> 15:38.344
- If this works,
I'll forgive you

15:38.413 --> 15:40.413
for letting it slip out
the door in the first place.

15:40.482 --> 15:42.172
- If this works,
you can forgive yourself

15:42.241 --> 15:44.034
for letting it slip out
the door in the first place.

15:44.103 --> 15:45.827
- Motherfucker, you was closer.

15:45.896 --> 15:49.137
- I was going for the morphine.
- Knock it off.

15:49.206 --> 15:51.172
[keys clacking]
- What happens if it's gone?

15:51.241 --> 15:52.724
- Then your ass belongs
to Sasquatch.

15:52.793 --> 15:56.034
- And that's no fun, trust me.
Holy shit!

15:56.103 --> 15:57.448
They're active.
It's still out there.

15:57.517 --> 15:59.000
- Yes!

15:59.068 --> 16:00.310
- They all have
the same coordinates.

16:00.379 --> 16:01.689
All the money's
still together.

16:01.758 --> 16:03.379
- Hell yes!
- Where--where is it?

16:03.448 --> 16:05.310
- Quit breathing down my neck.
I'm about to find out.

16:05.379 --> 16:06.931
- No matter where it is,
we're gonna find it.

16:07.000 --> 16:08.689
- Damn straight we are.

16:08.758 --> 16:10.827
- Yeah, there's another way.
There's always another way.

16:10.896 --> 16:13.310
- Never give up, do you?
- The fuck else am I gonna do?

16:13.379 --> 16:15.310
- Uh-oh.
- What uh-oh? Huh?

16:15.379 --> 16:17.586
- No more uh-ohs.
Where's my money?

16:17.655 --> 16:20.448
- These coordinates
would be right here.

16:23.448 --> 16:25.275
- Damn.
- Shit.

16:25.344 --> 16:28.000
- Fuck.
- Mm-hmm.

16:30.655 --> 16:32.275
- That's Taliban country,

16:32.344 --> 16:35.655
- Correction, it's right in
the heart of Taliban country.

16:40.586 --> 16:42.827
[tense music]

16:42.896 --> 16:44.655
- Did we get
the coordinates wrong?

16:44.724 --> 16:46.172
- We didn't.

16:46.241 --> 16:48.000
- Goddamn Navy SEALs
wouldn't venture in there.

16:48.068 --> 16:50.620
No way we'd make it in,
much less out.

16:50.689 --> 16:53.241
- What if it's just sat there
in a tree or something

16:53.310 --> 16:55.137
waiting for somebody
to find it?

16:55.206 --> 16:57.379
- Then that somebody is gonna
be the motherfucking Taliban.

16:57.448 --> 16:58.793
- It was worth a shot.

16:58.862 --> 17:00.344
- Fuck that.
I'm not giving up.

17:00.413 --> 17:02.275
- Of course you're not.
- But I am.

17:02.344 --> 17:04.310
Gotta go see a man
about a vest.

17:04.379 --> 17:07.379
- Hey, can you give me
a little more time?

17:07.448 --> 17:10.896
before you give Sasquatch
your fucking hat size?

17:10.965 --> 17:12.827
- Time is something
I ain't got.

17:12.896 --> 17:15.137
- Please.

17:16.310 --> 17:18.586
- You got 24 hours.

17:21.034 --> 17:23.103
- I can't let
that man down again.

17:23.172 --> 17:25.551
- Well, it looks like
you don't have a choice.

17:27.724 --> 17:29.620
- There's always a choice.

17:29.689 --> 17:32.586
[somber music]

17:32.655 --> 17:34.862
[sighs]

17:34.931 --> 17:37.655
♪ ♪

17:37.724 --> 17:42.034
[indistinct chattering]

17:42.103 --> 17:45.862
♪ ♪

17:45.931 --> 17:48.034
[knock on door]

17:48.103 --> 17:50.482
- You need to see this.

17:58.275 --> 18:00.206
- What am I looking at here,
Major?

18:00.275 --> 18:02.000
- Lab report on
the contamination

18:02.068 --> 18:04.896
of the drinking water from
the village I was found in.

18:04.965 --> 18:06.586
- I can't understand
a thing in here.

18:06.655 --> 18:08.344
- Then I'll summarize.

18:08.413 --> 18:11.862
The well water had extremely
high concentrations

18:11.931 --> 18:13.862
of Polychlorinated Biphenyls
in it.

18:13.931 --> 18:15.413
- That doesn't sound good.

18:15.482 --> 18:17.931
- It isn't,
and levels this high

18:18.000 --> 18:22.000
can cause seizures,
internal bleeding, and death.

18:22.068 --> 18:23.931
- And you think SecCorp
poisoned their water

18:24.000 --> 18:25.758
on purpose.

18:25.827 --> 18:27.137
- There are eyewitness accounts

18:27.206 --> 18:29.206
of SecCorp men
coming into the town

18:29.275 --> 18:31.275
and dumping unknown substances
into the wells.

18:33.827 --> 18:36.206
- Have a seat, Major.

18:49.965 --> 18:53.310
I'm getting ready to make
a move against SecCorp, Major.

18:53.379 --> 18:55.413
I believe they're responsible
for the death of a Corporal

18:55.482 --> 18:58.379
from this base named
John Buckley.

18:58.448 --> 19:00.206
Sergeant Roback's
After Action Report

19:00.275 --> 19:01.965
puts SecCorp in that village

19:02.034 --> 19:05.551
the very day
Buckley was killed.

19:05.620 --> 19:10.758
Your testimony would for sure
be the tipping point in opening

19:10.827 --> 19:14.310
an AR 15-6 investigation
into those bastards.

19:14.379 --> 19:16.827
- Yeah, well, obviously,
I'll do whatever I can to help.

19:21.862 --> 19:24.172
- In that case,
I need to know just one thing.

19:24.241 --> 19:25.655
- Yes, sir.

19:25.724 --> 19:27.620
- Are you willing to testify
as to what you saw

19:27.689 --> 19:29.689
and what happened to you
in that village?

19:29.758 --> 19:31.172
- Yes, sir.

19:31.241 --> 19:32.724
- I don't need to tell you
the dangers

19:32.793 --> 19:34.000
in going up against SecCorp.

19:34.068 --> 19:35.241
We'll both be placing

19:35.310 --> 19:37.931
our entire military careers
at risk.

19:38.000 --> 19:40.586
[suspenseful music]

19:40.655 --> 19:42.068
- I'm fully aware of

19:42.137 --> 19:43.482
and willing to take
those risks, sir.

19:43.551 --> 19:45.724
- I'm counting on that, Major.

19:45.793 --> 19:47.758
I'm not gonna be able
to do this alone.

19:47.827 --> 19:50.758
[somber music]

19:50.827 --> 19:57.517
♪ ♪

19:57.586 --> 19:59.620
- [sighs]

20:02.517 --> 20:04.551
- I got someone
I want you to meet.

20:06.206 --> 20:07.620
- A fix-up?

20:07.689 --> 20:09.517
You know I'm married.
Shame on you.

20:10.655 --> 20:12.068
- You're gonna wanna
come with me.

20:12.137 --> 20:14.482
- Where?
- Our side.

20:14.551 --> 20:17.689
- Ooh.
I've never been to your side.

20:17.758 --> 20:20.551
I hear it's pretty rockin'.
- Yeah, it is.

20:22.000 --> 20:24.000
- Heard you guys have
a juice bar, is that true?

20:24.068 --> 20:28.103
[suspenseful music]

20:28.172 --> 20:29.758
- [inhales sharply]

20:29.827 --> 20:32.000
- Sergeant Roback,
come on in.

20:32.068 --> 20:34.034
Have a seat.

20:34.103 --> 20:36.413
- I'd rather not.

20:36.482 --> 20:38.310
- Cappuccino?

20:38.379 --> 20:41.379
- No.
- Morgan Jennings.

20:41.448 --> 20:43.000
Executive Vice President,
SecCorp.

20:43.068 --> 20:46.344
- We've met.
Why am I here?

20:46.413 --> 20:48.862
- You are here
because your name

20:48.931 --> 20:51.172
keeps popping up
on my radar.

20:52.931 --> 20:54.344
- My apologies.

20:54.413 --> 20:57.206
- No, none needed.
It's impressive, actually.

20:57.275 --> 20:59.965
I mean, we run a very fairly
tidy operation,

21:00.034 --> 21:03.413
but you seem to have a knack
for gumming up the works.

21:04.896 --> 21:07.655
There's a lot of money at stake
with our operations here,

21:07.724 --> 21:10.000
and rather than having
you continue

21:10.068 --> 21:11.758
to be a fly in our ointment,

21:11.827 --> 21:14.068
I'd like to offer you
a position with us.

21:14.137 --> 21:16.103
- [chuckles]

21:16.172 --> 21:18.137
Nah, I'm good.

21:18.206 --> 21:19.689
I'd rather keep exposing
your weaknesses

21:19.758 --> 21:21.034
until you guys
are out of business.

21:21.103 --> 21:22.620
- Really?

21:22.689 --> 21:24.689
Like filing an After Action
Report that accuses us

21:24.758 --> 21:27.068
of the murder of
a United States Army Corporal?

21:27.137 --> 21:29.103
- How'd you know about that?

21:29.172 --> 21:30.965
- I run a very tidy operation.

21:31.034 --> 21:33.517
- You run a scam.

21:34.827 --> 21:36.551
You've been trying
to clear out that town

21:36.620 --> 21:38.206
with intimidation and force

21:38.275 --> 21:40.517
since the day you arrived
on this base,

21:40.586 --> 21:42.517
plus there was no other
enemy combatants anywhere

21:42.586 --> 21:44.620
near Buckley
when he was killed

21:44.689 --> 21:46.034
except your men.

21:46.103 --> 21:47.862
- I appreciate your passion,
Sergeant,

21:47.931 --> 21:51.344
but it's that passion
that makes me concerned

21:51.413 --> 21:53.758
for the grief you're gonna
cause me if you keep this up.

21:53.827 --> 21:56.172
- Be afraid.

21:56.241 --> 21:58.896
You and your whole
fucking organization

21:58.965 --> 22:01.586
desecrate the only reason
I'm proud to wear this uniform.

22:04.620 --> 22:08.482
- The last American hero
standing right before me.

22:08.551 --> 22:10.344
- Yeah, if the job interview
is over,

22:10.413 --> 22:11.827
I have a soufflé
in the oven.

22:11.896 --> 22:13.896
- Not quite!

22:17.758 --> 22:22.827
♪ ♪

22:22.896 --> 22:24.344
- What's this?

22:24.413 --> 22:25.793
- I don't know.
Take a look.

22:25.862 --> 22:28.448
I think you'll find it
as fascinating as I did.

22:38.068 --> 22:40.551
- Where'd you get this?
- We asked for it.

22:40.620 --> 22:42.310
That's how it works
with police reports.

22:42.379 --> 22:44.758
They're a matter
of public record.

22:44.827 --> 22:47.793
- Yeah.
He was killed by drug dealers.

22:48.965 --> 22:51.379
- But the case can be reopened.

22:51.448 --> 22:53.620
And the lead detective
on the case, by the way,

22:53.689 --> 22:55.551
a really nice guy.

22:55.620 --> 22:58.965
He's ready to remember a few
key details about the case

22:59.034 --> 23:01.241
that are going to paint
a vastly different conclusion

23:01.310 --> 23:03.655
as to who killed your father.

23:05.068 --> 23:08.241
I intend to be rid of you
one way or another.

23:08.310 --> 23:10.448
- Get in line.

23:10.517 --> 23:13.827
- Look, Sergeant.

23:13.896 --> 23:16.517
Sending you to prison
for murder?

23:18.137 --> 23:19.724
It's low-hanging fruit for us,

23:19.793 --> 23:23.517
but we can just leave
the fruit on the tree.

23:23.586 --> 23:26.241
All you have to do is rescind
your After Action Report

23:26.310 --> 23:29.827
and promise to stay out of our
business here at the base.

23:29.896 --> 23:32.344
- Is that all?

23:32.413 --> 23:34.103
- I mean,
the job offer still stands.

23:34.172 --> 23:35.620
Hell, I'll even--

23:35.689 --> 23:37.379
I'll put you to work
alongside your friend, uh...

23:37.448 --> 23:39.172
- Davis.
- Davis!

23:39.241 --> 23:40.517
There you go.

23:40.586 --> 23:42.379
The dream team
back together again.

23:42.448 --> 23:44.103
- Dream being
the operative word.

23:44.172 --> 23:45.931
- Oh, God, really?

23:46.000 --> 23:50.758
I am surprised someone
as vulnerable as you are

23:50.827 --> 23:52.827
would even consider
going against us.

23:54.482 --> 23:56.586
- I know.
It's dumb, right?

23:56.655 --> 23:58.655
- And all this
isn't gonna be good

23:58.724 --> 24:00.758
for that sham marriage
of yours.

24:02.620 --> 24:04.758
- Don't know what the fuck
you're talking about.

24:06.689 --> 24:08.620
- Oh, it must be one
of those open marriages

24:08.689 --> 24:10.482
because you and Corporal Durkin

24:10.551 --> 24:13.000
haven't been nearly
as discreet as you think.

24:13.068 --> 24:15.172
- [chuckles]

24:15.241 --> 24:19.655
♪ ♪

24:19.724 --> 24:21.551
You guys don't play very nice.

24:21.620 --> 24:24.034
- It's the only way
to get things done.

24:24.103 --> 24:25.793
- Not this time.

24:27.137 --> 24:28.586
- I see a resemblance.

24:28.655 --> 24:29.793
- You're about to find out

24:29.862 --> 24:31.689
there's absolutely
no resemblance.

24:38.689 --> 24:41.206
- Why do you have
to get involved?

24:41.275 --> 24:43.586
- I'm the evidence
of what they did,

24:43.655 --> 24:45.206
and I'm a Major.

24:45.275 --> 24:47.310
If I can make them pay
for it, I'm going to.

24:47.379 --> 24:49.103
- And what if you can't?

24:49.172 --> 24:50.862
These people don't like
to be interfered with,

24:50.931 --> 24:54.310
and they have connections that
run to the top of Washington.

24:54.379 --> 24:57.413
- I don't care.
I'm gonna fight them.

24:57.482 --> 25:01.103
- SecCorp will bury you
and everyone you care about.

25:01.172 --> 25:03.758
- What happened
to personal responsibility?

25:03.827 --> 25:05.724
What happened to character?

25:05.793 --> 25:07.413
- Major Holloway!

25:07.482 --> 25:09.482
- [sighs]

25:09.551 --> 25:11.103
What is it, Private?

25:11.172 --> 25:13.000
- Ma'am, we need you
at the suicide gate.

25:13.068 --> 25:15.103
There's a problem.

25:15.172 --> 25:16.551
- I just need
to speak with her.

25:16.620 --> 25:18.310
- You're about to have
30 rounds of ammunition

25:18.379 --> 25:19.965
in your fucking skull
if you do not step back!

25:20.034 --> 25:21.551
- Stand down, Corporal!

25:21.620 --> 25:23.724
- Ma'am, this local does not
have clearance to enter!

25:23.793 --> 25:26.655
- Stand down!
I'll handle it.

25:26.724 --> 25:28.172
What are you doing here?

25:28.241 --> 25:29.896
- I needed to know
that you were okay.

25:29.965 --> 25:31.724
- I'm fine.

25:31.793 --> 25:33.827
- I should have done something
when you were injured.

25:33.896 --> 25:36.344
I should have fought.
I did not.

25:36.413 --> 25:40.172
♪ ♪

25:40.241 --> 25:43.586
- It's time to say goodbye.

25:43.655 --> 25:45.896
[somber music]

25:45.965 --> 25:47.344
- Yeah.

25:47.413 --> 25:50.931
♪ ♪

25:51.000 --> 25:53.482
- Goodbye, Qasem.

25:54.724 --> 25:56.482
- Goodbye, Sonia.

25:56.551 --> 26:03.551
♪ ♪

26:17.206 --> 26:19.896
- Sup?
What's this?

26:19.965 --> 26:21.517
- What you asked me
to get for you.

26:21.586 --> 26:24.172
The latest insurgency
reconnaissance report from OSI.

26:24.241 --> 26:25.724
The nearest recorded
Taliban position

26:25.793 --> 26:27.827
to the exact coordinates
the money is signaling from

26:27.896 --> 26:28.931
is just over ten clicks away.

26:29.000 --> 26:30.448
- It's not that close.

26:30.517 --> 26:32.482
- No, it's not.

26:32.551 --> 26:33.931
- How fresh is the intel?

26:34.000 --> 26:36.241
- It just came in an hour ago.

26:36.310 --> 26:38.034
- Okay.

26:38.103 --> 26:39.551
I'm going in.

26:39.620 --> 26:41.034
- By yourself?

26:41.103 --> 26:42.551
- I'm not gonna ask
anybody else to take

26:42.620 --> 26:43.793
that kind of risk with me.

26:43.862 --> 26:45.896
- Are you suicidal?

26:45.965 --> 26:47.103
- I promised Davis
I'd do something.

26:47.172 --> 26:48.620
- What?
Get killed?

26:48.689 --> 26:50.344
'Cause that's
not gonna fix his problems.

26:50.413 --> 26:51.931
- Look, according to this
report, it's easy to get

26:52.000 --> 26:53.379
to this location,
check if the money's there,

26:53.448 --> 26:55.172
and get back out
before anybody notices.

26:55.241 --> 26:57.965
- Theoretically, yes.
- That's good enough for me.

26:58.034 --> 26:59.517
- You could still run
into enemy fire.

26:59.586 --> 27:01.034
- I could also not.

27:01.103 --> 27:03.000
- How are you gonna do this?

27:05.758 --> 27:07.758
- I can get an ambulance.

27:07.827 --> 27:11.000
It's really not that far.

27:11.068 --> 27:13.172
We're only a couple days out
from Ramadan.

27:13.241 --> 27:14.931
It'll be relatively quiet.
I'll go then.

27:15.000 --> 27:16.241
- I can't let you do this.

27:16.310 --> 27:18.310
- [scoffs]
Bullshit.

27:18.379 --> 27:19.931
You knew exactly what I'd do

27:20.000 --> 27:22.103
the second
you handed me this.

27:22.172 --> 27:24.862
- You know, you doing
insane shit like this

27:24.931 --> 27:27.482
is exactly what attracted me
to you in the first place.

27:27.551 --> 27:29.586
- [chuckles]

27:31.310 --> 27:33.172
Look, I need you
to do me a favor.

27:33.241 --> 27:35.931
- [sighs]
What?

27:36.000 --> 27:37.206
- Don't tell 'em
I'm doing this.

27:37.275 --> 27:38.655
- Why?

27:38.724 --> 27:39.965
- Because they're only gonna
try and talk me out of it.

27:40.034 --> 27:41.827
- That's a good thing.
- Grace.

27:41.896 --> 27:44.586
Promise me.

27:44.655 --> 27:47.103
♪ ♪

27:47.172 --> 27:49.000
- This is for Davis
and Alvarez.

27:49.068 --> 27:55.103
♪ ♪

27:55.172 --> 27:57.413
- You told me that you and I
were a lot alike.

27:57.482 --> 27:59.448
- So?

27:59.517 --> 28:03.689
- I didn't really get it.
I do now.

28:03.758 --> 28:05.965
♪ ♪

28:06.034 --> 28:07.275
- [chuckles]

28:07.344 --> 28:10.310
A little late, but okay.

28:11.862 --> 28:13.344
- Thank you, Corporal.

28:15.482 --> 28:17.586
- You're welcome, Sergeant.

28:17.655 --> 28:24.586
♪ ♪

28:29.310 --> 28:33.517
- You're not the only person
who's gone through this

28:33.586 --> 28:36.275
in a deployment.

28:36.344 --> 28:38.482
- You?

28:40.413 --> 28:42.448
Well, did you tell Mom?

28:42.517 --> 28:44.793
- She knew.

28:47.344 --> 28:50.034
- So you just went back home
and everything was the same?

28:50.103 --> 28:52.758
- Nothing was the same.

28:52.827 --> 28:58.000
We told ourselves we were
staying together

28:58.068 --> 29:00.206
for you and your brothers.

29:00.275 --> 29:01.965
But then when
she was diagnosed,

29:02.034 --> 29:07.862
we realized how much
we meant to each other, and...

29:10.655 --> 29:14.068
we just sort of fell in love
all over again.

29:16.448 --> 29:19.931
- [sighs]
Well, that's...

29:20.000 --> 29:22.724
really beautiful
and horribly sad.

29:22.793 --> 29:24.241
- And I'm telling you,

29:24.310 --> 29:26.517
your mother and I
did the right thing.

29:31.448 --> 29:34.551
Sonia, I know Will's
a bit of a pill.

29:34.620 --> 29:36.310
I told you that
when you got married,

29:36.379 --> 29:38.482
but he is a good man,

29:38.551 --> 29:41.586
and he is raising your sons
right now, selflessly.

29:46.931 --> 29:49.241
- [sighs]

29:51.344 --> 29:53.482
That call you mentioned?

29:53.551 --> 29:56.724
- Yeah?
- Make it.

29:56.793 --> 30:03.724
♪ ♪

30:03.793 --> 30:05.000
[knock on door]

30:05.068 --> 30:06.896
- Yup?

30:06.965 --> 30:08.793
- 24 hours is up, amigo.

30:09.758 --> 30:11.793
- Look, man, you've got to give
me a little bit more time.

30:11.862 --> 30:14.103
- No, man.
- No, just a couple of days.

30:14.172 --> 30:16.241
- I don't have
a couple of days.

30:16.310 --> 30:18.482
I don't even have
a couple of hours.

30:18.551 --> 30:19.965
- I can get you the money.

30:20.034 --> 30:23.689
- How?
- I'm working on it.

30:25.275 --> 30:26.896
- Look, man,

30:26.965 --> 30:29.034
you're the only guy I've called
my best friend

30:29.103 --> 30:30.931
since I was in
the second grade,

30:31.000 --> 30:32.310
but I need you
to understand

30:32.379 --> 30:33.896
that this has nothing
to do with you.

30:33.965 --> 30:36.655
- Look, I get that.

30:36.724 --> 30:38.931
I just wanna help you.

30:39.000 --> 30:41.000
- I need to do this.

30:41.068 --> 30:43.103
- [sighs]

30:43.172 --> 30:45.137
Look, I'm sorry I put you
in this position.

30:46.586 --> 30:48.310
You gave me a chance
with the hashish

30:48.379 --> 30:50.068
and I fucked that up.

30:50.137 --> 30:52.206
You gave me another chance
with the fight

30:52.275 --> 30:54.827
and I fucked that up too.

30:57.413 --> 31:01.310
But if you give me
this one last chance,

31:01.379 --> 31:04.896
I promise you
I can get you the money,

31:04.965 --> 31:06.931
but you gotta trust me.

31:08.931 --> 31:12.275
- I can't afford
to trust you anymore.

31:17.275 --> 31:18.862
- When are you gonna
tell Sasquatch?

31:18.931 --> 31:20.724
- I already did.

31:20.793 --> 31:24.206
♪ ♪

31:24.275 --> 31:26.034
- I understand.

31:26.103 --> 31:30.482
I understand why you can't
put your faith in me anymore,

31:30.551 --> 31:33.862
but I'm gonna come through
for you on this.

31:33.931 --> 31:36.413
And when I do, I want you
to take that bonus check

31:36.482 --> 31:38.206
and shove it up SecCorp's ass.

31:38.275 --> 31:40.310
♪ ♪

31:40.379 --> 31:42.827
- Nothing would give me
more pleasure.

31:42.896 --> 31:45.827
[chuckles]

31:45.896 --> 31:47.586
- [chuckles]

31:53.103 --> 31:54.620
- As soon as I get back,

31:54.689 --> 31:56.310
I'll make that phone call.

31:56.379 --> 31:58.310
And you can go back
to your family,

31:58.379 --> 32:01.068
and be a real presence
in your kids' lives.

32:01.137 --> 32:03.758
- Then pray Will comes down
with a terminal disease

32:03.827 --> 32:06.310
so I can fall in love
with him again?

32:06.379 --> 32:10.482
- Let's hope it won't come
to all that.

32:10.551 --> 32:13.413
- Yeah.
Let's hope.

32:13.482 --> 32:15.310
[helicopter engine whirrs]

32:15.379 --> 32:21.000
♪ ♪

32:21.068 --> 32:24.275
- The sacrifices you and I
have made for the greater good

32:24.344 --> 32:28.482
are more than anybody
could have asked.

32:30.068 --> 32:32.068
- I know.

32:32.137 --> 32:39.241
♪ ♪

32:59.827 --> 33:02.241
- Are you awake?

33:03.103 --> 33:05.448
- I am now.

33:05.517 --> 33:07.517
- Sorry.

33:15.655 --> 33:17.103
- [sighs]

33:17.172 --> 33:19.379
What's up?

33:21.724 --> 33:23.896
- I'm worried about my family.

33:25.344 --> 33:28.965
- Hey, it's all gonna be okay.

33:30.275 --> 33:32.827
- Why do you say that?

33:32.896 --> 33:37.413
- Because we're gonna get
the money to hire a good lawyer

33:37.482 --> 33:39.586
and we're gonna help them out.

33:40.896 --> 33:42.862
- How?

33:42.931 --> 33:44.655
- Somehow.

33:46.137 --> 33:48.965
- You seem very sure.
- I am.

33:49.034 --> 33:50.689
- Why?

33:53.000 --> 33:55.206
- I just am.

33:56.620 --> 33:58.551
I'm gonna figure this out.

34:00.931 --> 34:02.551
- How?

34:04.068 --> 34:06.103
- It's not your concern.

34:06.172 --> 34:07.655
[both chuckle]

34:07.724 --> 34:09.965
- I don't like the sound
of that.

34:10.034 --> 34:13.000
- Hey, it's gonna be okay.

34:14.379 --> 34:16.310
Get some sleep.

34:16.379 --> 34:22.862
♪ ♪

34:22.931 --> 34:24.448
Good night.

34:24.517 --> 34:26.172
- Good night.

34:26.241 --> 34:33.344
♪ ♪

34:36.206 --> 34:37.931
- [sighs]

34:38.000 --> 34:39.862
♪ ♪

34:39.931 --> 34:42.689
- Is this what it's like
to be married?

34:42.758 --> 34:44.551
- You mean when
one of us flips out

34:44.620 --> 34:46.758
and the other one tells them
it's gonna be okay?

34:48.275 --> 34:50.827
- [chuckles]
It's nice.

34:52.137 --> 34:53.827
♪ ♪

34:53.896 --> 34:57.758
- And it is
all gonna be okay.

34:57.827 --> 35:00.379
♪ ♪

35:00.448 --> 35:02.379
You'll see.

35:02.448 --> 35:06.310
♪ ♪

35:06.379 --> 35:07.896
- [sighs]

35:07.965 --> 35:14.896
♪ ♪

35:19.000 --> 35:22.206
- Hey, Babe,
you just caught me, but--

35:22.275 --> 35:24.482
sorry, I'm about to pick up
the kids from soccer practice.

35:24.551 --> 35:28.310
- Oh, it's okay.
I wanted to talk to you alone.

35:29.517 --> 35:31.448
- What happened?

35:31.517 --> 35:33.103
- Oh, nothing.

35:33.172 --> 35:35.586
I, um...

35:35.655 --> 35:38.310
Just moving too fast.

35:38.379 --> 35:40.551
Anyway, I wanted
to let you know that

35:40.620 --> 35:43.448
my deployment
isn't getting extended.

35:43.517 --> 35:46.379
- What?
- Yeah.

35:46.448 --> 35:48.103
I'm gonna be home sooner
than expected,

35:48.172 --> 35:50.000
a lot sooner.

35:50.068 --> 35:54.448
And I can't wait to see
you and the boys.

35:54.517 --> 35:56.482
So get ready.
[chuckles]

36:01.000 --> 36:03.206
- Uh, Sonia...

36:03.275 --> 36:05.206
- What's wrong?

36:05.275 --> 36:08.931
- Um, I, uh--oh, God.

36:09.000 --> 36:11.931
I don't know how to say this,

36:12.000 --> 36:15.068
but I guess it's best
said now like this.

36:15.137 --> 36:17.344
- Like what?

36:17.413 --> 36:20.034
- I've met someone else.

36:21.137 --> 36:22.931
- What?

36:24.275 --> 36:26.586
- Yeah.

36:27.689 --> 36:29.655
I...
[chuckles]

36:29.724 --> 36:33.931
I mean, we--we've
been apart for so long.

36:34.000 --> 36:36.758
You know, and...

36:36.827 --> 36:38.655
I mean, what did you think
was gonna happen?

36:38.724 --> 36:42.482
Every time I try
and connect with you,

36:42.551 --> 36:45.137
I just feel like, um...

36:45.206 --> 36:47.620
- [laughs]

36:49.034 --> 36:51.586
- Did you hear
what I just said?

36:51.655 --> 36:53.586
- Yes, I did.
I'm sorry.

36:53.655 --> 36:55.241
[clears throat]

36:55.310 --> 36:58.482
You know, maybe we should talk
about this later.

36:58.551 --> 37:01.448
You know, you should go
and get the boys,

37:01.517 --> 37:04.172
and, um, I will call you.

37:04.241 --> 37:06.034
I promise.

37:06.103 --> 37:08.413
[chuckles]

37:08.482 --> 37:10.965
I promise.

37:11.034 --> 37:12.413
[knock on door]

37:12.482 --> 37:13.965
- Great.
Okay.

37:14.034 --> 37:16.137
- What's so funny?

37:16.206 --> 37:19.034
- [sniffles, laughs]

37:19.103 --> 37:21.103
My husband is leaving me.

37:21.172 --> 37:23.482
[laughs]

37:23.551 --> 37:26.000
[soft rock music]

37:26.068 --> 37:27.689
♪ ♪

37:32.379 --> 37:35.172
[suspenseful music]

37:35.241 --> 37:42.344
♪ ♪

37:43.379 --> 37:46.034
[engine turns]

37:46.103 --> 37:48.275
- [sighs]

37:48.344 --> 37:52.103
♪ ♪

37:56.482 --> 37:58.068
What the fuck you guys
doing here?

37:58.137 --> 38:01.413
- Better question,
the fuck you doing here?

38:02.724 --> 38:04.413
- Just, uh, just had
the alternator replaced

38:04.482 --> 38:06.068
on this ambulance.

38:06.137 --> 38:07.758
Just gonna take it out
for a spin around the base

38:07.827 --> 38:09.517
to make sure it's all good.

38:09.586 --> 38:11.448
- Bullshit.
- You were going for the money.

38:11.517 --> 38:12.931
- [sighs]
Who told you that?

38:13.000 --> 38:14.068
- Oops.

38:18.655 --> 38:20.103
- Thank you, Corporal.

38:20.172 --> 38:21.931
- You're welcome, Sergeant.

38:23.068 --> 38:24.862
- Don't even try
and talk me out of this.

38:24.931 --> 38:28.034
- We're not gonna try it.
- Stand aside.

38:28.103 --> 38:30.517
- Durkin says Taliban sightings
in the area are sporadic.

38:30.586 --> 38:32.551
It's pretty unpopulated terrain

38:32.620 --> 38:34.655
according to the latest
OSI intel.

38:34.724 --> 38:36.655
- I may have given them a peek
at your report.

38:36.724 --> 38:38.310
- Thank you, Corporal.

38:38.379 --> 38:39.793
- You're welcome, Sergeant.

38:39.862 --> 38:42.068
- You're one foolish son
of a bitch, Roback.

38:42.137 --> 38:43.482
- True that.

38:43.551 --> 38:46.172
- Can't let you go alone.

38:46.241 --> 38:48.137
I'm going with you.

38:49.482 --> 38:52.689
- Yeah, me too.

38:52.758 --> 38:55.758
- And we ain't taking
no piece of shit ambulance.

38:55.827 --> 38:57.620
We gonna take the bird.

38:57.689 --> 38:59.310
In and out like lightning,
no questions asked.

38:59.379 --> 39:01.241
- Why?

39:01.310 --> 39:04.379
- You do this for us,
we do this for you.

39:04.448 --> 39:06.586
- Guys...
[chuckles]

39:06.655 --> 39:08.724
Fucking think about this.

39:08.793 --> 39:11.655
- If we think about it,
we don't do it.

39:11.724 --> 39:13.896
- There's a chance we may
not find that money.

39:13.965 --> 39:15.862
- Chance we might all
get killed.

39:15.931 --> 39:18.241
- Chance we might just make it.

39:19.241 --> 39:21.034
- And we can't trust that you
won't take all the money

39:21.103 --> 39:24.413
and just give it
to a fucking charity.

39:24.482 --> 39:26.758
- [chuckles]

39:27.758 --> 39:31.620
Either way, it's not for me.

39:31.689 --> 39:33.896
- You guys load up
from the armory.

39:33.965 --> 39:36.241
I'll draw up a flight plan.

39:36.310 --> 39:38.551
- Thank you.

39:40.310 --> 39:42.517
- There's no other crew
I'd rather put my life

39:42.586 --> 39:44.931
on the line for
except you guys.

39:45.965 --> 39:49.413
- No other crew.
- No other crew.

39:49.482 --> 39:52.000
- No other crew.

39:53.448 --> 39:56.310
- Don't look at me.
I'm not coming with you guys.

39:56.379 --> 39:59.689
Someone has to stay behind
and cover for you lunatics.

40:00.862 --> 40:02.551
- Meet you at the bird
at 0800.

40:02.620 --> 40:04.758
- ♪ True love to true love ♪

40:04.827 --> 40:07.137
♪ And rust to rust ♪

40:07.206 --> 40:08.827
♪ I let the others
cast stones ♪

40:08.896 --> 40:10.862
♪ While I drew in the dust ♪

40:10.931 --> 40:14.275
- Come on!
- Come on, Captain America.

40:14.344 --> 40:16.724
[laughter]

40:16.793 --> 40:21.241
- ♪ Old black magic
rolling in ♪

40:21.310 --> 40:23.586
♪ Rolling, rolling ♪

40:23.655 --> 40:26.172
♪ Rolling, rolling in ♪

40:26.241 --> 40:31.896
♪ ♪
